                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tips-content">
                <div class="tip-section" id="general">
                    <h2 class="tip-section-title">General Search Techniques</h2>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Finding Social Media Accounts</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Don't know their username? Start by searching their real name on each platform</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Username vs Display Name: Username is @johndoe123, Display Name is 'John Doe'</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Try variations: nicknames, initials, first name + graduation year</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check school social media pages for comments and tags</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for the same profile picture across different platforms</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="tip-highlight">
                            <div class="tip-highlight-title">Pro Tip</div>
                            <p>Many users maintain similar usernames across platforms. If you find an account on one platform, try searching for the same or similar username on other platforms.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Search Engines</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use multiple search engines (Google, Bing, DuckDuckGo) as they may yield different results</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Try specialized search engines like Social Searcher or Pipl for social media specific searches</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use quotation marks for exact phrase searches: "John Smith Springfield High"</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Add relevant keywords like school name, sports team, or graduation year</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use the site: operator to search specific websites (e.g., site:instagram.com "John Smith")</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-section" id="username">
                    <h2 class="tip-section-title">Username Search</h2>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Username Patterns</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Common patterns include: firstname.lastname, firstinitial_lastname, firstname_birthyear</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for usernames that include graduation year (e.g., jsmith2025)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check for usernames that include school mascots or sports team numbers</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Many users add underscores or periods between words in their username</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Some users replace letters with numbers (e.g., "a" with "4", "e" with "3", "i" with "1")</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="tip-example">
                            Common username variations for "John Smith":<br>
                            - johnsmith<br>
                            - john.smith<br>
                            - john_smith<br>
                            - jsmith<br>
                            - johnsmith2025<br>
                            - john.s<br>
                            - j.smith<br>
                            - j0hn5m1th
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Username Search Tools</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use tools like NameChk or KnowEm to check username availability across multiple platforms</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Try Sherlock, a command-line tool that searches for usernames across social networks</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">WhatsMyName is an open-source tool for username searches</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Google dorks to find specific username patterns (e.g., intext:@username site:twitter.com)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-section" id="boolean">
                    <h2 class="tip-section-title">Boolean Search Operators</h2>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Basic Boolean Operators</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">AND: Requires both terms to be present (e.g., John AND Smith)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">OR: Requires either term to be present (e.g., John OR Johnny)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">NOT: Excludes a term (e.g., Smith NOT John)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Quotation marks: Searches for an exact phrase (e.g., "John Smith")</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Parentheses: Groups terms together (e.g., (John OR Johnny) AND Smith)</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="tip-example">
                            Example Boolean search:<br>
                            ("John Smith" OR "Johnny Smith") AND "Springfield High" AND (basketball OR football) -teacher
                        </div>
                        
                        <p class="tip-note">This search would find mentions of John or Johnny Smith from Springfield High who plays basketball or football, but excludes results about teachers.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Advanced Search Operators</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">site: Limits results to a specific website (e.g., site:instagram.com)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">filetype: Searches for specific file types (e.g., filetype:pdf)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">inurl: Searches for text in the URL (e.g., inurl:johnsmith)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">intitle: Searches for text in the page title (e.g., intitle:"John Smith")</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">intext: Searches for text in the page content (e.g., intext:@johnsmith)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tip-section" id="image">
                    <h2 class="tip-section-title">Image Search</h2>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Reverse Image Search</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Google Images, TinEye, or Yandex for reverse image searches</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Try multiple reverse image search engines as they use different algorithms</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Crop the image to focus on the face or distinctive features before searching</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for the same profile picture used across different platforms</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check image metadata for location information or device details</li>
                        </ul>
                        
                        <div class="tip-highlight">
                            <div class="tip-highlight-title">Pro Tip</div>
                            <p>If a reverse image search doesn't yield results, try flipping the image horizontally or adjusting the brightness/contrast before searching again.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-subsection">
                        <h3 class="tip-subsection-title">Image Analysis</h3>
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for background details in photos that might reveal location information</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check for reflections in mirrors, windows, or sunglasses</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Examine clothing for school logos, team names, or other identifying information</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for consistent friends or locations across multiple photos</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Pay attention to timestamps and seasonal indicators in photos</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="platform-specific">
                    <div class="tip-section" id="instagram">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-instagram">IG</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">Instagram Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Search by username, full name, or hashtags</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check tagged photos to find connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look at followers and following lists for connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use location tags to find posts from specific areas</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check for Instagram stories highlights for additional content</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use third-party tools like Gramhir or Picuki to view profiles anonymously</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-section" id="tiktok">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-tiktok">TT</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">TikTok Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Search by username, nickname, or real name</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use hashtags related to schools, sports teams, or local areas</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check the "Friends" tab to see connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for duets and collaborations with other users</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use TikTok's "Discover" feature to find content by location</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check comments on popular local content</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-section" id="snapchat">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-snapchat">SC</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">Snapchat Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use the "Add Friends" feature to search by username or real name</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check Snap Map for location-based content</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for usernames that match patterns from other platforms</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use the "Quick Add" feature to find potential connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Search for public stories in specific locations</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check for Snapchat usernames shared on other social platforms</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-section" id="x">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-x">X</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">X (Twitter) Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Twitter's advanced search to filter by date, location, and keywords</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Search for mentions of usernames with the @ symbol</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use the "from:" operator to see all tweets from a specific user</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check who a user follows and who follows them</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for location tags in tweets</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Search for school hashtags or local event hashtags</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-section" id="discord">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-discord">DC</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">Discord Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Search for public Discord servers related to schools or local communities</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for Discord usernames shared on other platforms</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check for Discord links in gaming forums or social media profiles</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Discord's search feature within servers to find specific content</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Note that Discord usernames include a # followed by a number (e.g., username#1234)</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for Discord servers advertised on school websites or community pages</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tip-section" id="facebook">
                        <div class="platform-header">
                            <div class="platform-icon platform-facebook">FB</div>
                            <h2 class="platform-title">Facebook Search Tips</h2>
                        </div>
                        
                        <ul class="tips-list">
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Facebook's search filters to narrow results by city, education, or workplace</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check mutual friends to find connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Look for membership in school groups or local community groups</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Search for tagged photos to find connections</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Check event attendees for local school events</li>
                            <li class="tip-item">Use Graph Search syntax for advanced searches (e.g., "people who live in [city] and attend [school]")</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
